race.comment: BOYD (15) showed speed and was a close-up sixth on debut then again gave a sight when fourth last time. That has proved a hot form race with three winners and one minor from four subsequent starters. Has the inside here and expected to give a sight again. IBERIAN LYNX (3) has raced three times for three minors, fresh-up trying to lead throughout but finding one better. Fitter and will be in this for a long way. GIANT'S REPRIEVE (2) raced here over further before a break but looks well placed in this and will be winding up hard late. SHE'S ELUSIVE (11) is much better than last start when seventh in a richer maiden. Placed the start prior and gets chance to atone.
race.rail_position: +4m from the 400m to the winning post, True Remainder. (Pent: 5.60)
